{{Infobox company | name = Autocesta Rijeka - Zagreb d.d. | logo = File:Autocesta_Rijeka_–_Zagreb_logo.png | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. "fr" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. --> | former_name = | type = [[State-owned]] [[joint-stock company]] | industry = Road transport | founded = 1998 <!-- if known: {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} in [[city]], [[country]] --> | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location = | hq_location_city = [[Zagreb]] | hq_location_country = [[Croatia]] | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = | brands = | services = | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | website = [http://www.arz.hr/ www.arz.hr] }}
'''Autocesta Rijeka – Zagreb''' ({{lang-en|Rijeka - Zagreb Motorway}}) is a [[Croatia]]n state-owned joint-stock company founded pursuant to decision of the government of the Republic of Croatia of December 11, 1997, to facilitate construction and subsequent management of a motorway between [[Rijeka]] and [[Zagreb]].<ref name="ARZ-Founding">{{cite news|newspaper=[[Narodne Novine]] |language=Croatian |url=http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/1997_12_139_1994.html |title=Decision on founding of Rijeka - Zagreb Motorway joint stock company and granting of concession regulating construction and management of Rijeka - Zagreb motorway |date=December 11, 1997 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402134102/http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/1997_12_139_1994.html |archivedate=2015-04-02 |df= }}</ref> The company started operating on March 15, 1998. The company issued 21,520 shares, nominally valued at 100,000.00 [[Croatian kuna]] each. All company stocks are owned by the Republic of Croatia.<ref name="ARZ-General">{{cite news | newspaper = Autocesta Rijeka - Zagreb | language = Croatian | url = http://www.arz.hr/?page=2&lng=1 | title = ARZ general info | date = August 20, 2010}}</ref>
The company was granted the motorway management concession for a period of 28 years, which has subsequently been expanded to include not only the [[A6 (Croatia)|A6 motorway]] and some sections of the [[A1 (Croatia)|A1 motorway]], but also the [[A7 (Croatia)|A7 motorway]] and the [[Krk Bridge]] on the [[D102 (Croatia)|D102 state road]].<ref name="ARZ-Expansion">{{cite news|newspaper=[[Narodne Novine]] |language=Croatian |url=http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/2007_08_82_2585.html |title=Decision on amendments and additions to decision on founding of Rijeka - Zagreb Motorway joint stock company and granting of concession regulating construction and management of Rijeka - Zagreb motorway |date=August 2, 2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303204709/http://narodne-novine.nn.hr/clanci/sluzbeni/2007_08_82_2585.html |archivedate=2016-03-03 |df= }}</ref><ref name="Lider-ARZ">{{cite news | newspaper = Lider Press | language = Croatian | url = http://www.liderpress.hr/Default.aspx?sid=25291 | title = ARZ concession takes over Rijeka node | date = August 30, 2007}}</ref> The expansion of the concession also included extension of the concession period to 32 years and 11 months.
The company currently manages or develops the following routes:
{| class="wikitable" |- ! Number ! [[Control cities]] ''(or other appropriate route description)'' |- | {{Jct|country=HRV|A|1}} | [[Bosiljevo 2 interchange|Bosiljevo]] (A6) - [[Zagreb bypass|Lučko]] (A3) |- | {{Jct|country=HRV|A|6}} | Bosiljevo (A1) - [[Rijeka]] |- | {{Jct|country=HRV|A|7}} | [[Rupa, Croatia|Rupa]] border checkpoint - [[Rijeka]] (A6) - [[Sveti Kuzam]] - [[Križišće]] |- | {{Jct|country=HRV|D|102}} | [[Krk Bridge]] ''(maintenance and bridge toll collection)'' |}
{{As of|2018}}, the company is managed by a supervisory board.<ref name="ARZ-Structure">{{cite news |newspaper= Autocesta Rijeka - Zagreb |language= Croatian |url= https://www.arz.hr/hr/o-nama/kontakt |title = ARZ kontakt | accessdate = May 1, 2018}}</ref>
