{{Infobox central bank |bank_name_in_local = Banco de Cabo Verde |image = |image_title = |headquarters = [[Avenida Amílcar Cabral|Av. Amílcar Cabral]], [[Praia]], Cape Verde |established = 29 September 1975 |president = João Serra |leader_title = Governor |bank_of = [[Cape Verde]] |currency = [[Cape Verdean escudo]] |currency_iso = CVE |reserves = |borrowing_rate = |deposit_rate = |website = {{url|http://www.bcv.cv}} |preceded = |succeeded = |footnotes = |coordinates = {{coord|14.9188|-23.5091|display=it}} }}
The '''Bank of Cape Verde''' ({{lang-pt|Banco de Cabo Verde}}) is [[Cape Verde]]'s [[central bank]]. Its headquarter is located on [[Avenida Amílcar Cabral]], in the national capital of [[Praia, Cape Verde|Praia]] on the island of [[Santiago, Cape Verde|Santiago]].<ref>[http://www.bcv.cv/vEN/Footer/Paginas/Contactos.aspx Contacts], Banco de Cabo Verde</ref> Its current governor is João António Pinto Coelho Serra, who is in office since December 2014.<ref>[http://www.bcv.cv/Style%20Library/BCV/swfs/Organo/Scripts/Curriculum_Vitae_Governador.pdf CV Governador], Banco de Cabo Verde</ref>
==History== The government established the Bank of Cape Verde in 1975, as a bank that combined commercial banking and central banking functions. The government created the bank by nationalizing the operations of the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] colonial and overseas bank, [[Banco Nacional Ultramarino]], which had established its first branch in Cape Verde in 1865. In 1993, the government split off the [[commercial bank]]ing functions into the newly established [[Banco Comercial do Atlântico]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bcv.cv/vEN/thebank/Historia/Paginas/Historia.aspx|title=History of the Bank of Cape Verde|publisher=Bank of Cape Verde|language=en|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>
