===Custards=== [[Custard]] is a variety of culinary preparations based on a cooked mixture of [[milk]] or [[cream]] and [[egg yolk]]. Depending on how much egg or thickener is used, custard may vary in consistency from a thin pouring [[sauce]] ([[crème anglaise]]) to a thick pastry cream (crème pâtissière) used to fill [[Éclair (pastry)|éclairs]]. Most common custards are used as [[dessert]]s or [[dessert sauce]]s and typically include [[sugar]] and [[vanilla]]. Custard bases may also be used for [[quiche]]s and other savory foods. Sometimes [[flour]], [[corn starch]], or [[gelatin]] is added as in pastry cream or ''crème pâtissière''.
