{{Infobox language |name=Msər |altname=Kuseri |states=[[Cameroon]], [[Chad]] |region=[[Far North Province]], Cameroon; west Chad |speakers=500 in Cameroon |date=2004 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[Biu–Mandara languages|Biu–Mandara]] |fam4=[[Kotoko languages|Kotoko]] (B.1) |fam5=South |iso3=kqx |glotto=mser1242 |glottorefname=Mser }}
'''Mser''' (Msər), or '''Kousseri''' (Kuseri), is a moribund [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in northern [[Cameroon]] and southwestern [[Chad]]. Dialects are Gawi, Houlouf, Kabe, Kalo, Mser (Kuseri).
