[[File:Persconferentie in Nieuwspoort (5537900932).jpg|240px|thumb|Prime Minister Mark Rutte in front of the Nieuwspoort journalists]]
The '''Nieuwspoort''' (English: News gate) is a society catered to Dutch politicians, lobbyists and journalists so they can informally meet here.<ref>[http://www.nieuwspoort.nl/en_US/news/21/193/News-is-exchanged-here Nieuwspoort - News is exchanged here]</ref> It's also a place where press conferences from politicians (most notably the [[Prime Minister of the Netherlands]]' weekly address)<ref name="TrouwGeheim">{{cite web|url=http://www.trouw.nl/tr/nl/5133/Media-technologie/article/detail/3222337/2012/03/08/Het-geheim-van-Nieuwspoort.dhtml|title=Het geheim van Nieuwspoort|work=TROUW}}</ref> are held.

==History==
The press centre was opened in 1962 by [[Jo Cals]].<ref name="TrouwGeheim" /> Many notable incidents took place here, including the [[pieing]] incident during the book release of [[Pim Fortuyn]]'s ''[[De puinhopen van acht jaar Paars#Pieing_incident|De puinhopen van acht jaar Paars]]'' and [[Ayaan Hirsi Ali]]'s retirement announcement.<ref name="TrouwGeheim" />

