{{Infobox airport | name = Selebi-Phikwe Airport | nativename = | image = | IATA = PKW | ICAO = FBSP | pushpin_map = Botswana | pushpin_map_caption = Location of airport in Botswana | pushpin_label = '''PKW''' | type = Public | owner = | operator = Government | city-served = [[Selebi-Phikwe]], [[Botswana]] | location = | elevation-f = 2925 | elevation-m = | coordinates = {{coord|22|03|30|S|27|49|45|E|region:BW_type:airport}} | website = | metric-rwy = y | r1-number = 12/30 | r1-length-m = 1780 | r1-length-f = | r1-surface = Asphalt | footnotes = Sources: CAA Botswana<ref name="DCA">[http://www.caab.co.bw/caab-content.php?cid=258 Airports: Selebi-Phikwe] CAA Botswana</ref> WAD<ref>{{WAD|FBSP|Selebi Phikwe Airport}}</ref> GCM<ref name="GCM">{{GCM|PKW|Selebi-Phikwe}}</ref> }}
'''Selebi-Phikwe Airport''' {{airport codes|PKW|FBSP}} is an airport serving [[Selebi-Phikwe]], a town in the [[Central District (Botswana)|Central District]] of [[Botswana]]. Both the town and airport names are sometimes given as '''Selebi Phikwe'''.
The Selebi Phikwe [[non-directional beacon]] (Ident: '''SP''') is located on the field.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ourairports.com/navaids/SP/Selebi_Phikwe_NDB_BW/#lat=-22.05299949645996,lon=27.80430030822754,zoom=10,type=Satellite|title=Selebi Phikwe NDB (SP) @ OurAirports|website=ourairports.com|access-date=2018-08-20}}</ref>
The airport is {{convert|12|km}} southeast of the city. It is also near the gateway of the [[Tuli Block]] area, where wildlife and resorts are popular. No scheduled services currently operate at the airport. Private and charter traffic serve the airport.
==See also== *{{portal-inline|Botswana}} *{{portal-inline|Aviation}} *[[Transport in Botswana]] *[[List of airports in Botswana]]
